[This report of the involvement of multiple enteric pathogens suggests to
me the possibility of contamination of the town's water supply with raw
human sewage rather than just farm runoff. Prior conclusions about the
inadequacies of water treatment procedures and reporting of problems with
the water supply are unchanged by these observations. The presence of
former turkey processing facilities downstream from the water supply could
also be related via contamination of underground aquifers that are not
truly downstream. - Mod.ES
